22/03/2006
BANJA LUKA, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- Republika Srpska's government adopted and forwarded to parliament on Tuesday (21 March) amendments envisioning the launch of a special court and prosecutors to handle organised crime cases.
Prime Minister Milorad Dodik said the amendments were aimed at strengthening the fight against organised crime, a priority of the new cabinet.
Also Tuesday, the government approved changes in the privatisation law and forwarded them to parliament.
(Nezavisne novine - 22/03/06;
RTRS - 21/03/06)
